features: 120 GSM THICK DOTTED PAPER - Interior pages 80lb text 120gsm weight that resists ink bleed and ghost. Dot note book pages with smooth surfaces, which can bring you better writing and drawing experience. 3 pack includes blue, pink, and transparent. 64 sheets/ 128 pages per pack. Total 384 Pages! Each dot notebook measures 8.5 x 11 inches, inner paper size is 8.4 x 11 inches. Good sized to throw into your backpack for on-the-go note-taking.

PERFORATED PAGES - Perforated sheets make it easy to tear out assignments. Sheets measure 11" x 7.8" when torn out. You can stick the subject name on the notebook with free 5 Pieces multicolor tabs for easier finding information.

STURDY TRANSPARENT COVERS - Journal notebook covers are a firm, waterproof frosted plastic. They do not bend backwards easily, which is to protect the pages. And the plastic hard cover makes it tough enough to draw or write when you're standing. You can also DIY your own cover on the first page.

DOUBLE SPIRAL DESIGN - The spiral binding is sturdy but flexible. You can lay it flat and wrap it back so you're only working on one side at a time and can hold it upright while standing when writing. The diameter of the spiral binding is big enough to hold a pen on your note book.

GIFTABLE & WIDE USAGE - Great gift for school children, female friends or artist. You can use these dot grid spiral notebooks for note taking, working, journaling, creative writing, doodling and drawing, and much more.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Cover For Dotted Page Journal
reviews.reviewText: I love these notebooks. It's hard to find a good dotted page notebook that isn't expensive, and these are perfect. The covers are sheer and stay closed with an elastic strap, but the strap doesn't warp the shape of the notebook like others sometimes do. The paper quality was better than I expected for the price!

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Thick paper & my new fav!
reviews.reviewText: These are absolutely my new favorite notebooks. The paper is super thick the perforations work really well the spiral bound is sturdy… I’ve used this for note, taking, doodling, journaling, testing ink of new markers and brush pens, I use it for designing room layouts with the dot grid, I will draw some thing and color it and outline it and then I’ll cut it out and use it as a design in my journaling notebook to paste into it… I’ve spent a lot of money and I’ve searched high and low for really good quality paper and I absolutely love these.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great product, but prone to damage
reviews.reviewText: The notebooks are very good for the price. However, I got my package and all 3 notebooks were damaged(they were moderetely bent). The pink and white notebooks had spirals that ripped the pages too. The quality of the notebooks is really good; the paper is very nice and thick, nothing is loose, everything as expected. The notebooks are lightweight and exactly as pictured. The only compalint is the way they were packaged. There was no wrapping or a buffer between the product and the box it came in. I had to return, but I am definitely reordering!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Notebook of excellent quality at a great price.
reviews.reviewText: I use spiral notebooks for retention of information gathered in my work. There is frequent opening and wrapping front to back to enable the notebook easier to use while standing. Unlike typical spiral binders, the pages are of heavier weight, ink does not bleed through the underside of the page and pages do not indiscriminately tear out o the binder. The cover is a heavier material with a cord wrap to secure closure. Best spiral notebook for my purposes!

I adore these bujo flavored notebooks! I am tempted to buy a whole bunch before they become priced at what they are worth.To start off, I am a horrid paper snob and also spend a large portion of my day writing, doodling, listing, pretending to be working, etc. on paper. However, being a paper snob/el-cheapo, I have found it difficult to find "Archer & Olive" quality at dollar store prices... Until now!If my house was clean-ish, I would totally take pictures to go alongside this post. Because I love the semi-transparent cover, which allows one to create a really lovely cover page for their notebook. Also, no stress if ya' screw it up because you can just take that page out! Whoop whoop.The pages are nice and thick, none of my drawings have ghosted. I am unsure about paints, but I have high hopes, based on how the paper has responded to the markers and pens tried thus far.I am definitely purchasing another set of these as soon as I finish this post.
